CAPE TOWN &#8211; South Africa&#8217;s top manufacturing union Numsa said late on Monday that 600 workers out of 1 500 at General Motors SA will lose their jobs by July after a decision last week by the car maker to sell its local operations.The National Union of Metalworkers of South Africa (Numsa) said in a statement that GM had confirmed the numbers and issued lay-off notices as required by law. 